<subSubSection id="C33060C0FF84FFDE84B14757FBD50AE8" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B95334BFF84FFDD84B14757FCAB0935" blockId="13.[714,1247,807,1666]" box="[714,845,807,833]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">REMARQUES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95334BFF84FFDD84B14738FC7C0C8B" blockId="13.[714,1247,807,1666]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
À l’origine ont été décrites deux espèces, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD82024738FC000988" authority="(Lesueur, 1813)" baseAuthorityName="Lesueur" baseAuthorityYear="1813" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD82024738FCFF0988" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Cavolinia inflexa</emphasis>
(Lesueur, 1813)
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD826B4718FC7C09A8" authority="(d'Orbigny, 1836)" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD826B4718FB390988" box="[1040,1247,872,898]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Cavolinia labiata</emphasis>
(d’Orbigny, 1836)
</taxonomicName>
, et une entité infraspécifique 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD84B147D8FC6309C8" baseAuthorityName="Lesueur" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[714,901,936,962]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD84B147D8FC6309C8" box="[714,901,936,962]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Cavolinia inflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forma 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD85A247D8FB3D09C8" authority="(Pfeffer, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Pfeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[985,1243,936,962]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Hyalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="imitans">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85A247D8FBCF09CB" box="[985,1065,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">imitans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4EBAFF84FFDD824247D8FB3409C8" author="PFEFFER G." box="[1081,1234,936,962]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" pagination="69 - 99" refId="ref26838" refString="PFEFFER G. 1880 - Die Pteropoden des Hamburger Museums. Abh. Ver. Hamburg 7: 69 - 99." type="journal article" year="1880">Pfeffer, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Ces trois taxons sont considérés depuis plusieurs décennies comme des sous-espèces pouvant former une série continue, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD85A34078FC9B0E48" authority="inflexa (Lesueur, 1813)" authorityName="inflexa (Lesueur" authorityYear="1813" baseAuthorityName="Lesueur" baseAuthorityYear="1813" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="inflexa" subSpecies="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85A34078FB380E28" box="[984,1246,1032,1058]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Cavolinia inflexa inflexa</emphasis>
(Lesueur, 1813)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85F04057FC5B0E4B" box="[907,957,1063,1089]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C. i.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD85BD4058FB240E48" authority="(Pfeffer, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Pfeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[966,1218,1064,1090]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Hyalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="imitans">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85BD4058FBF30E4B" box="[966,1045,1064,1089]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">imitans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB4EBAFF84FFDD825E4058FB5C0E48" author="PFEFFER G." box="[1061,1210,1064,1090]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" pagination="69 - 99" refId="ref26838" refString="PFEFFER G. 1880 - Die Pteropoden des Hamburger Museums. Abh. Ver. Hamburg 7: 69 - 99." type="journal article" year="1880">Pfeffer, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
et 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD84B14037FD1A0E6B" box="[714,764,1095,1121]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C. i.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD857D4038FBD50E68" authority="(d'Orbigny, 1836)" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[774,1075,1096,1122]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD857D4038FCB40E68" box="[774,850,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">labiata</emphasis>
(d’Orbigny, 1836)
</taxonomicName>
. L’existence de variations clinales et de divisions subspécifiques chez 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD857F40F8FC270EA8" baseAuthorityName="Lesueur" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[772,961,1160,1186]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD857F40F8FC270EA8" box="[772,961,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Cavolinia inflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ont récemment été réfutées: les variations observées ne seraient pas d’ordre géographique mais dues aux différences de croissance et de disponibilités en nourriture (Spoel &amp; Pierrot-Bults 1998). Nos observations personnelles nous permettent, au contraire, de redonner à 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD853C4137FC480F68" baseAuthorityName="Lesueur" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[839,942,1351,1378]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD853C4137FC480F68" box="[839,942,1351,1378]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C. inflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD85A94137FBDA0F68" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[978,1084,1351,1378]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85A94137FBDA0F68" box="[978,1084,1351,1378]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C. labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
un rang spécifique. Les formes actuelles de 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD82614117FB600F88" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[1050,1158,1383,1410]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD82614117FB600F88" box="[1050,1158,1383,1410]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C. labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
présentent quelques variations qui ne justifient pas momentanément la création de taxons infraspécifiques. Par contre, nous décrivons une sousespèce fossile 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD850B4197FBA60C08" authority="Rampal, 2002" authorityName="Rampal" authorityYear="2002" box="[880,1088,1511,1538]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="labiata" status="n. ssp." subSpecies="robusta">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD850B4197FC640C0B" box="[880,898,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85EF4198FBA60C08" box="[916,1088,1512,1538]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">labiata robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26D5222FF84FFDD82304197FB710C0B" box="[1099,1175,1511,1537]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="subSpecies">n. ssp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Nous conservons à 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD85134277FC310C28" baseAuthorityName="Lesueur" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[872,983,1543,1570]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85134277FC310C28" box="[872,983,1543,1570]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C. inflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, les deux sous-espèces 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD84B14257FCA20C48" box="[714,836,1575,1602]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
C. i. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD84854258FCA20C48" baseAuthorityName="Lesueur" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[766,836,1576,1602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexa">inflexa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
et 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD851E4257FC010C4B" box="[869,999,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
C. i. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD85E24258FC010C4B" baseAuthorityName="Pfeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[921,999,1576,1601]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Hyalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="imitans">imitans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Enfin, nous décrivons deux espèces fossiles: 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD85AB4237FB930C68" authority="Rampal, 2002" authorityName="Rampal" authorityYear="2002" box="[976,1141,1607,1634]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="longicostata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD85AB4237FC040C6B" box="[976,994,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD858F4238FB930C68" box="[1012,1141,1608,1634]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">longicostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26D5222FF84FFDD82FB4237FB260C6B" box="[1152,1216,1607,1633]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF84FFDD84B14217FCBE0C88" authority="Rampal, 2002" authorityName="Rampal" authorityYear="2002" box="[714,856,1639,1666]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pachysoma" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD84B14217FD3A0C8B" box="[714,732,1639,1665]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF84FFDD84914218FCBE0C88" box="[746,856,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">pachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26D5222FF84FFDD85254217FC7C0C8B" box="[862,922,1639,1665]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95334BFF87FFDE86EC44D7FEB5084B" blockId="14.[151,684,167,1665]" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">
Nos observations concernent des milliers d’individus et notre analyse statistique plusieurs centaines de spécimens, actuels pour la plupart, mais aussi fossiles et sur lesquels ont été mesurés de nombreux paramètres par une méthode de reconnaissance de formes. Les spécimens actuels proviennent de la plupart des secteurs océaniques (
<figureCitation id="13112FCEFF87FFDE87F045F8FE0A0BA8" box="[395,492,392,418]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="21.[151,162,1259,1276]" captionTargetBox="[226,1178,169,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[209,1185,123,1236]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIG. 8. — Groupe inflexa; A, B, variations clinales de Cavolinia inflexa imitans (Pfeffer, 1880), superposition de spécimens méditerranéens (A) et atlantiques (B) C, projection de l’analyse factorielle sur les plans factoriels I et II; 1 -5, Méditerranée; 6, 7, Atlantique Portugais et Marocain; 8, Indien; 9, Atlantique sud-oriental; 10, Pacifique occidental; 11, Atlantique sud-occidental; 12, Atlantique Nord, Pacifique occidental et centre-équatorial; D, répartition géographique des différents taxons. Abréviations: Ciim, Cavolinia inflexa imitans (Pfeffer, 1880); Ciin, C. i. inflexa (Lesueur, 1813); Cl, C. labiata (d’Orbigny, 1836); H, hauteur; l, largeur; L, longueur; Lp, longueur de l’épine postérieure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5394248" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5394248/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
), les fossiles, de dragages dans l’océan 
<collectingCountry id="F33D73DBFF87FFDE87D345D8FE130BC8" box="[424,501,424,450]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">Indien</collectingCountry>
sud-occidental et aussi de carottages en Méditerranée nordoccidentale (sédiments prélevés dans les 19 premiers cm des sédiments) et orientale (jusqu’à 
<quantity id="4CD29EAEFF87FFDE86824658FEA1084B" box="[249,327,551,578]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="223" unit="cm" value="36.0">36 cm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95334BFF87FFDE86EC4637FF0C0C8B" blockId="14.[151,684,167,1665]" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">
Les configurations obtenues sur les plans factoriels I et II (
<figureCitation id="13112FCEFF87FFDE87584618FE9C0888" box="[291,378,616,642]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="21.[151,162,1259,1276]" captionTargetBox="[226,1178,169,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[209,1185,123,1236]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIG. 8. — Groupe inflexa; A, B, variations clinales de Cavolinia inflexa imitans (Pfeffer, 1880), superposition de spécimens méditerranéens (A) et atlantiques (B) C, projection de l’analyse factorielle sur les plans factoriels I et II; 1 -5, Méditerranée; 6, 7, Atlantique Portugais et Marocain; 8, Indien; 9, Atlantique sud-oriental; 10, Pacifique occidental; 11, Atlantique sud-occidental; 12, Atlantique Nord, Pacifique occidental et centre-équatorial; D, répartition géographique des différents taxons. Abréviations: Ciim, Cavolinia inflexa imitans (Pfeffer, 1880); Ciin, C. i. inflexa (Lesueur, 1813); Cl, C. labiata (d’Orbigny, 1836); H, hauteur; l, largeur; L, longueur; Lp, longueur de l’épine postérieure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5394248" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5394248/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
) permettent de caractériser deux ensembles relativement homogènes situés dans deux cadrans opposés: d’une part, l’ensemble de l’Indo-pacifique occidental et central, correspondant à 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF87FFDE87F24698FDA30908" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[393,581,744,770]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="223" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF87FFDE87F24698FDA30908" box="[393,581,744,770]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">Cavolinia labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; d’autre part, l’ensemble de l’Atlantique sud-occidental, Atlantique nord et Pacifique sud-oriental central et occidental correspondant à 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF87FFDE843F4738FED30988" authority="inflexa" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="223" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="inflexa" subSpecies="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF87FFDE843F4738FED30988" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">Cavolina inflexa inflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On observe aussi un troisième ensemble de l’Atlantique, Méditerranée, Pacifique oriental. Il est formé d’une série de nuages imbriqués, correspondant à 
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF87FFDE844047B7FF240E0B" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">
C. i. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF87FFDE840647B8FF240E0B" baseAuthorityName="Pfeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Hyalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="223" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="imitans">imitans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Parmi la quarantaine de paramètres pris en compte, seules la largeur au niveau des épines latérales (l) et la longueur de l’épine postérieure (Lp) ont une forte valeur discriminante. Elles ont des projections assez fortes sur l’axe II: l est localisé dans un nuage de point de la forme 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF87FFDE875040D8FE480ECB" authority=", Lp" authorityName="Lp" box="[299,430,1191,1217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Hyalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="223" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="imitans">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF87FFDE875040D8FE9A0ECB" box="[299,380,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">imitans</emphasis>
, Lp
</taxonomicName>
dans un nuage de la forme 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF87FFDE869240B8FED10EE8" box="[233,311,1224,1250]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="223" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflexa">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF87FFDE869240B8FED10EE8" box="[233,311,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">inflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Leurs valeurs relatives l/L et Lp/L corroborent cette distribution. La longueur (L) et la hauteur (H) sont proches de l’axe II et n’ont pas de valeur discriminante ainsi que les autres paramètres qui n’appparaissent pas dans le graphe. Les caractéristiques de la face dorsale (côte, lèvre, sinuosité) établissent d’emblée une discrimination entre 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A48C8FF87FFDE844541D8FF020FE8" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Gastropoda" family="Cavoliniidae" genus="Cavolinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pteropoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="223" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis id="B95EEF59FF87FFDE844541D8FF020FE8" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="223">Cavolinia labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et les deux autres entités. Elles interviennent dans nos descriptions mais n’entrent pas dans les calculs mathématiques d’ordre biométrique qui nous ont permis de suivre l’évolution de la silhouette de l’ensemble du groupe.
</paragraph>
